[August 2011]

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #95) (not yet released)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Second speed improvement of the Html widget: double buffering implemented.
But this feature needs testing.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #94)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Severe error with marks in si3::Consumer and si3::Encoder fixed.
* Severe errors in overview.tcl and browser.tcl fixed.

* On Fedora systems the truetype fonts will be installed in /usr (not
/usr/local).

* Database upgrade implemented (not yet used).

* Focus problem in tree game list solved.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #92)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Bug item #3381510 fixed.
* Bug item #3381580 fixed.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #91)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* m_types.h updated: g++ versions < 4.6 are not really ready for C++0x
standard (previous patch failed).

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #90)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* m_types.h updated: g++ versions < 4.6 are not really ready for C++0x
standard.

[July 2011]

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #89)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* First speed improvement of the Html widget (highlighting). The slowness
seems to be a general problem if a large window is involved, but this needs
further investigation.

* Comment parsing and tokenizing fixed.

* Update problem with game header fixed.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #87)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Event info popup implemented (ButtonPress-2).

* Problem with fullscreen mode fixed (bug item #3369168).

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #86)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Upgrade to C++0x standard.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #81)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Invalid date entries in .si3/4 bases will be refused now.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #80)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Busy cursor stuff reimplemention refined.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #79)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Busy cursor stuff reimplemented.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #77)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Bug with bottom space underneath board (hopefully) fixed (bug item #3349601)

* Engines added (MicroMax and TogaII-1.3.1).

* tkmenu.tcl changed: modernized menu behavior, but only available under
windoze (modernized does not mean "better").

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #76)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* configure script changed, hopefully it will now detect versions >= 4.5 of
the gnu compiler.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #71)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Correction of variation folding: a folded variation does not show comments
anymore.

* Eco translation from Fernando integrated. Both translation now are macRoman
encoded.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #70)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* startHtmlElement() fixed (game recovery should be correct now).

* Game header of recovered games ok now.

* Problem with black castling on main board fixed (bug item #3356896).

* The configure script will now add -fno-stack-protector option if supported;
Ubuntu 11.04 has stack protection on per default, but I dont want this; makes
the program slower and is satisfying only the paranoid people.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scidb 1.0 BETA (rev. #69)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Game list: Shift-Double-Button-1 will switch to the board tab after loading
the game (see feature request #3349617).

* web::open reimplemented, see bug item #3349635.

* Scidb is now remembering the icon size (already fixed in rev. #68).

* PGN reader will warn about failed encoding only once.

* Encoding problems with PGN files fixed (default encoding is ISO8859-1).

* Checksum computation fixed: the game bar should not load anymore an already
open game.

* <Shift-Double-Button-1> bound to game list on database tab: switch to the
main board when loading a game.
